														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1159674">
									

<p>I like the concept, but nothing here really feels new. There's already an alien/unnatural ecosystem <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-440">SCP-440</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-217">SCP-217</a> covers the clockwork angle. I think this needs a rewrite to make it more unique from those two.</p>
<p>I want to know more about the ecosystem aspect. Most of this SCP sounds like it's just a robo-bug generator, but then you touch on a food-chain and stuff. That sounds like it could be very interesting, and would help round out concept, give it some depth. I don't really want a list of bugs, I want to know how the ecosystem functions as a whole, and why, if got loose, it would be a problem. How quickly do the herbivore machines eat, were these machines found in just one room, stuck in a loop of eating only themselves, or were they spreading slowly from the clock?</p>
<p>I'm not going to vote, because I don't <em>dis</em>like it, but it needs something more.</p>

							</div>

								
					
