														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1160028">
									

<p>Even worse, it seems obvious to me that since the automata are capable of adapting to changing circumstances, if the clock were permitted to run down, they'd find an alternate source of energy. And most modern houses are just <em>filled</em> with electrical outlets. And if you cut off the power to the house, well, it is possible to extract energy from decaying corpses, like the researchers&#8230; and anyone else in that town&#8230;</p>
<p>Upvoted. One suggestion, however: I would recommend changing one line, to state that the design is &quot;precise to a degree not previously thought to be humanly possible.&quot; Obviously, unless 343 made these things, their design <em>was</em> humanly possible. :)</p>

