			<div class="content" id="post-content-1160054">
									

<p>There is a conflict in the containment/description:</p>
<p>Under Containment - <em>any containment breach will likely end without intervention, as SCP-816 requires access to SCP-816-1 in order to survive, and is not capable of moving SCP-816-1</em></p>
<p>Under Description - <em>without SCP-816-1, SCP-816 would likely adapt to gain energy in a way that would allow it to expand beyond Site-P/██</em></p>
<p>One should be changed. Since they are dependent on it, I would suggest that the Containment be changed to have Agents periodically winding the Grandfather Clock to remove the possibility of a breach.</p>

